00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:28,200
It's an sms with asian characters, I don't know what language. And...

230
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:34,440
And yesterday when I sat on Youtube, I was logged out.

231
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:39,000
My partner asked: "Does this usually happen?" It has not happened in eight years -

232
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:44,480
-That I was suddenly logged out of Google and Youtube.

233
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:47,720
So that was weird.

234
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:53,880
The hackers realize that there's no time to both steal Therese's password-

235
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:59,160
–And get past her two-factor- authentication. The hack is canceled.

236
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:06,440
-Hello. -Hello! Hey!

237
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:10,400
-How's it going? -Good.

238
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:15,040
You have on the street met a dad to a fan.

239
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:18,440
-Yes!.

240
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:21,600
I was so happy too.

241
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:26,480
And then I got an email from his daughter and became so happy.

242
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:32,160
I clicked the link, because she had seen something in a video. I clicked.

243
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:34,840
What happened then?

244
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:40,640
It came up that I should fill in my details. So I closed it.

245
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:45,560
–Ah ... - We sent you phishing emails.

246
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:48,200
The goal was to get you to click -

247
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:54,720
-And hopefully, sometime when you're not so alert, log in–

248
00:20:54,880 --> 00:21:00,960
-And then we hope that the details were used elsewhere.

249
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:06,440
Oh, no! Was it phishing, phishing- email, when you send out links?

250
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:10,640
-Exactly. "Nätfiske" in Swedish. -I understand.

251
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:14,520
Very well done, Therese!

252
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:19,640
This was very unpleasant, but it was very interesting.

253
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:23,040
I have learned a lot about reflecting.

254
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:27,320
- Very kind of you, Therese. -Thank you so much for today.

255
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:32,520
We all need to improve our security on the internet, talk about it.

256
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:36,720
We need to educate ourselves and each other.

257
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:41,920
We need to make demands on politicians for major efforts -

258
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:45,160
- when it comes to our IT security.

259
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:48,440
They need to give more money to the police–

260
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:53,160
So that they can investigate and prevent crime on the internet.

261
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:56,360
These are important issues.

262
00:21:56,520 --> 00:22:01,160
Passwords must be unique. That is the most important thing.

263
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:06,320
Because if one service gets hacked, you only need to change that password-

264
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:10,720
- and wont risk something happening on the other sites.

265
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:16,040
The second is that it must be long - at least 12-15 characters.

266
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:20,240
The children's names - no. The dog's name or the registration number - no.

267
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:24,200
123456 - no, come on!

268
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:28,520
Rather than a character soup you can use a phrase. You can have:

269
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:32,840
"MyMotherSangForMeOnce- WhenIWasSleeping".

270
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:39,480
The longer, the harder it is to crack. It is easier to remember phrases.

271
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:44,640
But we shouldn't have to remember passwords - use password manager!

272
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:50,080
There are countless of them. find out your needs, and choose tools.

273
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:57,920
–Hey! Good work! -So damn nice!

274
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:03,640
The breakthrough came when my computer cracked the password to his key chain.

275
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:08,000
It was a combination of his old password "hatasj" -

276
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:15,120
And the birth year of one of his children. Then the treasure chest opened: key chain.

277
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:21,280
Now we all have passwords in the key chain. We have Chrome login passwords.

278
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:26,520
We have to decrypt it now, because it contains more passwords.

279
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:33,760
David managed to decrypt it and the secrets just poured out.

280
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:39,440
We all have passwords for Chrome Extensions now. Everything!

281
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:43,080
–The works! –162 different ones. Good.

282
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:48,200
-We can login to Instagram, right? -What nasty tricks should we do?

283
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:52,520
-I think a picture is fun. - I can check Facebook.

284
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:54,680
He has to put up with a bit of mischief.

285
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:59,520
We take a picture where we stand with a sign: "Double passwords."

286
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:02,440
Are you ready? Smile.

287
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:10,920
Ten hours has passed since the hackers infected Kristoffer's computer.

288
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:17,120
Now Jesper can be himself. It's time to reveal himself.

289
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:21,840
-Hello! My name is Jesper. -Welcome.

290
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:27,600
I work as an IT security specialist - you probably already understood that.

291
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:30,920
-I have. - You look a bit confused.

292
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:35,120
No, but ... I think we have had contact during the day.

293
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:40,160
- I got some emails because of you. -That's probably true.

294
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:44,640
-At least the last few hours. -Right.

295
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:49,480
- Have you noticed anything else? -I think Instagram, Facebook and ...

296
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:53,920
- Can we check Instagram now, or? -Yes absolutely.

297
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:59,840
Damn, you didn't post on Instagram? -No no no....

298
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:04,040
Check the latest post. Are you nervous, or?

299
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,480
-Yes of course. No worries, it's safe for work.

300
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:11,160
Do you recognize anyone? / JESPER LAUGHS /

301
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:15,840
Thank you very much. It says "double passwords".

302
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:22,200
Proof that I was owned, It hurt little.

303
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:26,760
I'm not an IT manager at some damn security company.

304
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:31,280
-I'm a clown. -But a pretty good clown.

305
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:36,480
But I didn't do this alone, I had help. Here they are.

306
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:39,880
Can you see us? You're frozen.

307
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:43,480
-Yes now. Hey! -Hello!

308
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:47,640
David and I were in the hotel room and joined via Teams.

309
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:50,720
We could control his computer from there.

310
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:54,440
- Do you have your computer in front of you? -I do.

311
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:56,920
Is there something on your screen now?

312
00:25:57,080 --> 00:26:01,600
I opened this document that I had-

313
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:06,760
- with over 100 usernames and password, on the screen.

314
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:10,320
–Shit! - You need triple passwords.

315
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:17,160
Thanks. I knew this would come back and bite me in the ass.

316
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:23,400
It was fun hacking Kristoffer, since Svenska Nyheter is quite provocative.

317
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:25,560
He took it well.

318
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:30,720
But ... oh yeah. It's pretty frustrating, because it's not just my passwords.

319
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:34,040
It's SVT's password -

320
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:39,240
-Which I have been given as trade secrets. Damn, this sucks!

321
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:42,480
But you know? I'm also super happy.

322
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:49,680
Because if I had this list, I would have save so much time!

323
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:54,320
I've agreed to this, so not much to whine about.

324
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:58,560
It's an eye opener how all your stuff is connected.

325
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:03,880
"I have that password there too, so if someone finds it "...

326
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:09,160
